WEBVTT

00:08.269 --> 00:11.228
[eerie music]

00:11.272 --> 00:13.448
♪

00:13.491 --> 00:14.536
[beeps]

00:14.579 --> 00:16.842
- We're ready for you,
Dr. Brock.

00:16.886 --> 00:22.848
♪

00:22.892 --> 00:24.937
- [sighs]

00:34.295 --> 00:37.907
- Mr. Lang,
what's your story?

00:37.950 --> 00:41.737
- Um, my, um,
my right ankle hurts.

00:41.780 --> 00:43.304
- Uh-huh.

00:58.275 --> 01:01.496
- Leslie Varick,
what's your story?

01:01.539 --> 01:03.541
- Don't you remember me,
Doctor?

01:03.585 --> 01:05.587
I've been coming here
a long time.

01:05.630 --> 01:08.242
- I'm sorry.
Crazy day.

01:08.285 --> 01:10.418
Where does it hurt?
- My knee.

01:10.461 --> 01:12.289
Ugh.
Here.

01:13.812 --> 01:15.292
- Mm-hmm.

01:18.078 --> 01:20.906
- Thank you, Doctor.
I knew you'd understand.

01:20.950 --> 01:23.605
You're just the best.

01:23.648 --> 01:30.612
♪

01:30.655 --> 01:31.917
- [sighs]

01:42.450 --> 01:44.887
[exhales]

01:52.634 --> 01:54.636
[sighs]

02:20.531 --> 02:23.012
- Hey!
The hell are you doing?

02:23.055 --> 02:25.406
[gunshots]

02:38.854 --> 02:40.812
[sighs]

02:40.856 --> 02:43.859
- [wheezing]

02:46.905 --> 02:50.692
Justin, help me.

02:50.735 --> 02:54.086
[strained breathing]

02:59.396 --> 03:00.702
[gunshot]

03:00.745 --> 03:03.792
- What was that?
Hello?

03:03.835 --> 03:05.881
Hello?

03:05.924 --> 03:08.057
Hello?

03:10.146 --> 03:12.670
Are you still there?

03:13.410 --> 03:16.500
Ma'am, are you still there?

03:16.544 --> 03:18.546
Is Justin your husband?

03:18.589 --> 03:21.418
Stay with me.
A unit is on the way.

03:22.941 --> 03:26.423
[tense music]

03:30.949 --> 03:33.517
- Wind's about right.

03:33.561 --> 03:35.606
- Okay, now take off the jess.

03:35.650 --> 03:38.174
- Can I pet him first?
- Of course.

03:41.003 --> 03:43.484
- Good-bye, Wally.
[chirps]

03:49.664 --> 03:51.883
- Give him a nudge.

03:51.927 --> 03:53.581
Go on.

03:58.194 --> 04:00.718
- He's flying strong.

04:00.762 --> 04:02.154
Just like new.

04:02.198 --> 04:03.939
- What if he wants
to come back?

04:03.982 --> 04:05.506
- He won't.

04:05.549 --> 04:07.421
Up there's
where he wants to be.

04:07.464 --> 04:09.727
That's why we nursed him
back to health,

04:09.771 --> 04:12.556
so he could do
what he does best.

04:12.600 --> 04:16.560
[phone ringing]

04:16.603 --> 04:19.476
- It's okay, Dad.
Go to work.

04:20.216 --> 04:22.436
- You heard the boss.
Go on.

04:22.479 --> 04:24.829
All right.
- [giggles]

04:24.873 --> 04:26.178
- Agent LaCroix.

04:26.222 --> 04:27.963
- Ready, set, go.

04:28.006 --> 04:29.965
- I'm on my way.

04:30.008 --> 04:32.097
[Nelson & Tali laughing]
- Cheater!

04:32.141 --> 04:34.622
- The criminal
investigative division

04:34.665 --> 04:37.146
put Dr. Brock on the
Most Wanted list this morning.

04:37.189 --> 04:39.844
The headlines are:
two homicides and a fugitive

04:39.888 --> 04:42.804
with the resources and means
to flee the jurisdiction.

04:42.847 --> 04:44.458
- Not to mention
the medical skills

04:44.501 --> 04:45.981
to set himself up
in a foreign country.

04:46.024 --> 04:47.548
- And the unlawful flight
warrant

04:47.591 --> 04:48.810
should be here any minute.

04:48.853 --> 04:50.202
In terms of the number
of fugitives

04:50.246 --> 04:51.987
that have made
our Most Wanted list,

04:52.030 --> 04:53.989
I did not check
where Brock stands--

04:54.032 --> 04:56.644
- He's number 524
on the hit parade.

04:56.687 --> 04:58.254
- But who's counting?

04:58.298 --> 04:59.864
- Well, I look forward
to this task force

04:59.908 --> 05:02.214
putting him on this list.

05:04.869 --> 05:06.610
- Brock found his wife
in the kitchen,

05:06.654 --> 05:08.133
shot twice by the intruder.

05:08.177 --> 05:10.266
He then finished her off
with the intruder's gun.

05:10.310 --> 05:11.876
But get this:

05:11.920 --> 05:14.183
Mrs. Brock managed to call 911
on her cell.

05:14.226 --> 05:17.186
The operator heard her identify
Brock before he shot her.

05:17.229 --> 05:19.493
- Bummer for Brock.

05:19.536 --> 05:21.625
- When the Newburgh cops
turned up 15 minutes later,

05:21.669 --> 05:24.062
Brock was gone and the family
safe was cleaned out.

05:24.106 --> 05:25.586
- Tell me about the intruder.

05:25.629 --> 05:27.588
- The late Glenn Ericks,

05:27.631 --> 05:29.894
priors for burglary
and weapons possession.

05:29.938 --> 05:32.157
Associated with
a local biker gang.

05:32.201 --> 05:33.507
- And Brock's family?

05:33.550 --> 05:34.769
- Step-daughter.

05:34.812 --> 05:36.597
This was a second marriage
for him.

05:36.640 --> 05:39.600
Divorced his first wife
12 years ago.

05:39.643 --> 05:41.166
- Where are we
on the U-FAP warrant?

05:41.210 --> 05:43.691
- Just got in.
We're good to go.

05:43.734 --> 05:45.867
- We're looking for
girlfriends, boyfriends,

05:45.910 --> 05:48.565
anyone with a personal
or business hook with Brock.

05:48.609 --> 05:51.176
Hana, deep dive on
background, social media,

05:51.220 --> 05:53.527
sites for naughty husbands.
Crosby!

05:53.570 --> 05:55.703
If you could put that protein
bar down long enough--

05:55.746 --> 05:57.095
- Hey, I'm a growing boy.

05:57.139 --> 05:58.749
- Did you say you have
a growing butt?

05:58.793 --> 06:01.230
- Check Brock's phone records,
texts, emails.

06:01.273 --> 06:04.538
Clinton: malpractice suits,
financials, side businesses.

06:04.581 --> 06:05.887
I wanna know what Brock's done,

06:05.930 --> 06:07.628
and I wanna know
who he's done it with.

06:07.671 --> 06:10.587
Barnes and I will start
with the step-daughter.

06:10.631 --> 06:14.243
Now, don't underestimate
this fugitive.

06:14.286 --> 06:16.637
He might look like a foot
doctor who's in over his head,

06:16.680 --> 06:18.247
but he got the drop
on an ex-felon,

06:18.290 --> 06:20.989
and he executed his wife
in cold blood.

06:21.032 --> 06:23.557
Skill and depravity.

06:23.600 --> 06:26.560
We have to consider him
capable of anything.

06:26.603 --> 06:29.911
[dramatic music]

06:29.954 --> 06:31.652
- I don't get it.

06:31.695 --> 06:33.262
I--I thought Mom and Justin
were happy together.

06:33.305 --> 06:35.873
- They were married six years?
- Yes.

06:35.917 --> 06:38.572
I just didn't see it.
- You didn't see what?

06:38.615 --> 06:41.879
- How bad things must've been
for him to do this.

06:41.923 --> 06:43.881
I just assumed she was happy.

06:43.925 --> 06:46.797
We used to talk all the time
until she married Justin.

06:48.146 --> 06:50.932
- Did they have
a vacation home anywhere?

06:50.975 --> 06:53.282
- No; why, you think
he left the country?

06:53.325 --> 06:54.631
- We'll catch him.

06:55.415 --> 06:56.851
Do you know
any of his friends?

06:56.894 --> 06:58.635
- I don't know
if he had any.

06:58.679 --> 07:00.811
He said he was too busy
to have a social life.

07:00.855 --> 07:03.205
- What did you think of him?

07:03.248 --> 07:06.164
- I thought he was boring,
but he spoiled my mom.

07:06.208 --> 07:08.689
He bought her this house.
He supported her causes.

07:08.732 --> 07:10.604
- Veterans' causes?
- Yes.

07:10.647 --> 07:11.953
He was a veteran himself.

07:11.996 --> 07:13.694
That's why Mom
got interested in him.

07:13.737 --> 07:16.827
Plus, he was a doctor too.
She felt so lucky.

07:16.871 --> 07:19.787
- Is that where they met,
at a veterans benefit?

07:19.830 --> 07:22.311
- No, on a blind date.

07:22.354 --> 07:26.097
Mom was the one who got him
involved in the charities.

07:26.141 --> 07:28.186
She was so giving.

07:30.667 --> 07:32.974
[sobs]

07:33.017 --> 07:35.150
It doesn't make sense.

07:35.193 --> 07:36.978
I'm sorry.

07:37.021 --> 07:39.241
[sobs]

07:39.284 --> 07:44.681
♪

07:44.725 --> 07:46.814
- Whatever was doing
between Brock and his wife,

07:46.857 --> 07:48.859
they kept it to themselves.

07:49.773 --> 07:51.862
Nothing like a man in uniform.

07:51.906 --> 07:53.908
- I think Brock would agree.

07:59.087 --> 08:00.175
- His legal
and financial records

08:00.218 --> 08:01.742
are as clean as whistle.

08:01.785 --> 08:03.178
No complaints
with the medical board.

08:03.221 --> 08:04.875
- And nothing popped
in his phone records.

08:04.919 --> 08:06.311
Texts, emails,
they'd put my grandma to sleep.

08:06.355 --> 08:08.096
- His social media
put me to sleep.

08:08.139 --> 08:09.837
I've never seen so many
pictures of shrimp cocktails.

08:09.880 --> 08:11.447
- Bottom line,

08:11.491 --> 08:12.970
there was no sign he was gonna
step out on his wife.

08:13.014 --> 08:14.668
- I don't see how
he'd have time.

08:14.711 --> 08:17.061
He was seeing
50 to 70 patients a day.

08:17.105 --> 08:19.237
There must be a lot of bunions
in Newburgh.

08:21.196 --> 08:22.763
- This is Ms. Augustin,
Brock's nurse.

08:22.806 --> 08:24.112
- Agent LaCroix.

08:24.155 --> 08:26.201
This is Agent Crosby,
Agent Barnes.

08:26.244 --> 08:28.377
Thanks for coming in; this
must've been a shock to you.

08:28.420 --> 08:30.901
- Yes, very much.
- Have you been with him long?

08:30.945 --> 08:32.903
- Since he opened the clinic
four years ago.

08:32.947 --> 08:34.905
- We need to see
Dr. Brock's office.

08:34.948 --> 08:36.994
- He was a two striper
in the 12th infantry.

08:37.038 --> 08:39.388
My regiment.
Served in Bosnia.

08:39.431 --> 08:40.998
- He's very proud
of his service.

08:41.042 --> 08:42.739
- We noticed.

08:44.741 --> 08:46.874
- What was in this drawer?
- Cash.

08:46.917 --> 08:49.006
A lot of his patients
paid in cash.

08:49.050 --> 08:51.269
- And Dr. Brock kept
it all in his office?

08:51.313 --> 08:52.880
- They paid him directly.

08:52.923 --> 08:54.708
He liked to do
his own bookkeeping.

08:54.751 --> 08:56.057
It's not my area.

08:57.275 --> 08:58.886
- What's in here?

08:58.929 --> 09:00.975
- Prescription pads.
- Do you have a key?

09:01.018 --> 09:05.283
[investigative music]

09:05.327 --> 09:07.242
- I don't understand.

09:07.285 --> 09:09.374
There were at least a hundred
pads under there two days ago.

09:09.418 --> 09:12.377
- None of these patient files
have any medical histories:

09:12.421 --> 09:15.032
no blood work,
no X-rays, no MRIs.

09:15.076 --> 09:17.513
What exactly did Dr. Brock do
for his patients?

09:17.557 --> 09:19.123
- He treated them.

09:19.167 --> 09:21.996
They presented with ankle pain,
foot pain.

09:22.039 --> 09:23.345
- And he treated them
without any tests,

09:23.388 --> 09:25.086
or maybe it didn't matter.

09:25.129 --> 09:27.871
He just wrote them
a prescription for painkillers.

09:27.915 --> 09:30.134
Is that what this was,
Ms. Augustin:

09:30.178 --> 09:32.441
an opioid pill mill?

09:32.484 --> 09:35.879
- I don't know, I just did
what Dr. Brock told me to do.

09:35.923 --> 09:38.099
- What was his fee
for writing a scrip?

09:38.142 --> 09:41.276
- His basic consultation
is $300.

09:41.319 --> 09:43.452
- Just for writing his name?

09:43.495 --> 09:45.323
- Maybe he thinks
he can bankroll his run

09:45.367 --> 09:47.543
by selling scrips for opioids.

09:47.587 --> 09:50.111
- [sighs]

09:50.154 --> 09:51.982
Let's start with
his most loyal patients.

09:54.289 --> 09:57.161
- Why are you talking to me?
I didn't do nothing wrong.

09:57.205 --> 09:59.773
I had good reason
to see Dr. Brock.

09:59.816 --> 10:01.818
- Just tell them the truth,
Mom.

10:01.862 --> 10:03.298
He was giving you pills.

10:03.341 --> 10:04.995
You're an addict,
and you can't admit that.

10:05.039 --> 10:06.562
- Cassie, please.

10:08.259 --> 10:11.393
I have injuries.
I have chronic pain.

10:11.436 --> 10:14.135
Look, I injured my knee.

10:14.178 --> 10:16.267
See?
- Those scars are old.

10:16.311 --> 10:19.140
How'd you do that?
- It was an accident.

10:19.183 --> 10:21.185
It wasn't no big deal.

10:22.143 --> 10:23.971
- How long
has she been an addict?

10:24.014 --> 10:25.886
- No, you leave her
out of this.

10:26.843 --> 10:28.149
- Three years.

10:28.192 --> 10:31.195
♪

10:31.239 --> 10:34.155
- [clears throat]
You tried talking to her?

10:34.198 --> 10:37.158
- All the time.
I beg her to stop.

10:37.201 --> 10:39.073
She's too out of it to care.

10:39.116 --> 10:41.597
- All those years
you still go to school,

10:41.641 --> 10:43.294
you do your homework every day?

10:45.470 --> 10:47.298
You're a strong person, Cassie.

10:47.342 --> 10:49.910
- Cassie, please,
I try my best.

10:50.432 --> 10:51.999
You have a roof
over your head.

10:52.042 --> 10:54.001
- Yeah, because
we're living at Grandpa's.

10:54.044 --> 10:56.394
♪

10:56.438 --> 11:00.311
There are times when I still
see the Mom I used to know.

11:01.965 --> 11:04.881
And other times--

11:04.925 --> 11:07.884
I just want you
to be my mom again.

11:07.928 --> 11:14.935
♪

11:16.066 --> 11:17.546
- How 'bout it, Leslie?

11:17.589 --> 11:20.114
You can start right now.
You can help us catch Brock.

11:20.157 --> 11:22.943
- I don't know where he is.
- Then how'd you get these?

11:22.986 --> 11:25.032
Prescription for Oxynet,

11:25.075 --> 11:27.164
filled yesterday at a pharmacy
in Pennsylvania.

11:27.208 --> 11:29.384
Isn't Oxynet
what Brock gives you?

11:29.427 --> 11:31.386
- He gave me the prescription,
not his clinic.

11:31.429 --> 11:33.605
- On Monday, this was yesterday
in Pennsylvania.

11:33.649 --> 11:35.085
Why Pennsylvania?

11:35.129 --> 11:36.347
- Come on, Leslie,
tell the truth.

11:36.391 --> 11:38.610
- I am.
He has another clinic.

11:38.654 --> 11:41.918
[tense music]

11:41.962 --> 11:44.355
- Federal agents.
We have a warrant.

11:44.399 --> 11:47.881
- There's no Dr. Brock here.
This is Alan Ashworth's clinic.

11:47.924 --> 11:49.404
- And who's this?

11:49.447 --> 11:51.232
- That's Dr. Ashworth.
He's a back specialist.

11:52.450 --> 11:54.975
- Ashworth was Lilian Brock's
maiden name.

11:55.018 --> 11:58.413
A Pennsylvania medical license
was issued to Dr. Alan Ashworth

11:58.456 --> 11:59.675
two years ago.

11:59.719 --> 12:01.416
- Brock's car is out back.
Engine's cold.

12:01.459 --> 12:03.331
He keep another car here?
- An Audi.

12:03.374 --> 12:05.028
- Color?
- Silver.

12:05.072 --> 12:06.029
- I'll get BOLO out.

12:06.073 --> 12:09.076
Silver Audi, get it.

12:09.119 --> 12:11.687
- Brock's patients are gonna be
mighty disappointed.

12:11.731 --> 12:14.385
There's so many of them.
- Enough to fill two clinics.

12:14.429 --> 12:16.431
Where does he find
all these people?

12:17.693 --> 12:19.390
Good morning.

12:19.434 --> 12:22.132
Did you bring money
for your appointment today?

12:22.176 --> 12:23.917
Can I see it, please?

12:23.960 --> 12:26.006
Don't worry,
you're not in any trouble.

12:26.049 --> 12:29.009
[tense music]

12:29.052 --> 12:33.535
♪

12:33.578 --> 12:36.407
- $50 bills.
Lower profile than Benjamins.

12:36.451 --> 12:37.495
- Hm.

12:40.150 --> 12:41.499
All right, folks, listen up.

12:41.543 --> 12:43.545
We're not here to
cause any trouble for you,

12:43.588 --> 12:45.286
but somebody's been
taking advantage

12:45.329 --> 12:46.722
of your circumstances.

12:46.766 --> 12:49.464
You good people can help us
do our job,

12:49.507 --> 12:51.118
and you'll be on your way.

12:51.161 --> 12:55.209
Now, $300 in $50 bills.

12:55.252 --> 12:56.776
Is that what everybody has?

13:01.171 --> 13:02.738
Excellent.
Thank you.

13:02.782 --> 13:05.132
Now, who gave you this money

13:05.175 --> 13:07.308
and sent you here
to see the doctor?

13:10.006 --> 13:12.269
Any takers?

13:12.313 --> 13:19.320
♪

13:25.369 --> 13:26.675
I couldn't help notice

13:26.718 --> 13:28.198
some of the ladies
are looking at you.

13:28.242 --> 13:30.679
♪

13:30.722 --> 13:32.507
- Maybe 'cause
I'm good lookin'.

13:32.550 --> 13:35.162
- [laughs]
You're not that good lookin'.

13:35.205 --> 13:37.120
How'd you get here
this morning?

13:37.164 --> 13:39.296
- I drove my pick-up.

13:39.340 --> 13:41.429
- You left your hog at home?

13:43.387 --> 13:46.477
The scuff marks on your boots
are from a Harley gear shifter.

13:49.219 --> 13:51.613
What's that ink on your arm?

13:53.441 --> 13:55.399
[suspenseful music]

13:55.443 --> 13:58.011
- Hey!
[grunting]

13:58.054 --> 14:00.056
- Whoa, whoa, whoa, whoa,
whoa, whoa, whoa!

14:00.100 --> 14:01.579
Hey, hey, hey, hey.
We got him, we got him.

14:01.623 --> 14:03.755
We got him.
It's all right, it's all right.

14:03.799 --> 14:05.409
- [breathing heavily]

14:05.453 --> 14:07.411
Turn over.
Turn over!

14:07.455 --> 14:09.326
[breathing heavily]

14:09.370 --> 14:10.458
Yeah.

14:11.372 --> 14:14.201
- Forsaken Sons.
Don't let him move.

14:15.419 --> 14:17.726
The intruder
who shot Brock's wife,

14:17.769 --> 14:19.380
what bike gang
did he belong to?

14:19.423 --> 14:21.686
- Glenn Ericks.
"Forsaken Sons."

14:23.340 --> 14:26.039
- Forsaken Sons.

14:26.082 --> 14:28.041
- Maybe that's who's recruiting
patients for Brock.

14:28.084 --> 14:29.390
- He's in business with 'em.

14:29.433 --> 14:31.131
With partners like that,

14:31.174 --> 14:33.437
he's got the means and
the muscle to avoid capture.

14:39.443 --> 14:40.967
[police radio chatter]

14:41.010 --> 14:42.751
- Gil Rickman
and the Forsaken Sons

14:42.794 --> 14:44.274
like to wrap themselves
in the flag

14:44.318 --> 14:46.059
and ride in veterans parades.

14:46.102 --> 14:48.583
It's just a cover for gun
running, drugs, prostitution.

14:48.626 --> 14:50.063
But this connection
with Dr. Brock,

14:50.106 --> 14:51.629
that's a new one on us.

14:51.673 --> 14:54.110
- Near as we can tell,
the gang recruited addicts

14:54.154 --> 14:56.460
to get a scrip
for Oxynet from Brock,

14:56.504 --> 14:57.461
and then they'd
walk the patient

14:57.505 --> 14:58.506
to a pharmacy to fill it,

14:58.549 --> 14:59.986
they'd give the patient a tip

15:00.029 --> 15:01.683
and sell the rest of the pills
on the street.

15:01.726 --> 15:03.511
- Brock and his gang
were clearing around

15:03.554 --> 15:06.514
$800 per prescription, 70 times
a day for the last four years.

15:06.557 --> 15:09.343
Brock was making
28 grand per day.

15:09.386 --> 15:11.388
- Lilian Brock knew Rickman
from her work with veterans

15:11.432 --> 15:13.042
before she married Brock.

15:13.086 --> 15:14.783
She probably introduced them.

15:14.826 --> 15:16.350
- Maybe she found out

15:16.393 --> 15:18.004
what Rickman and her husband
were up to?

15:18.047 --> 15:19.701
She wasn't havin' it,
so Brock had her killed.

15:21.398 --> 15:23.531
- His whole identity was
wrapped up in this heroic image

15:23.574 --> 15:24.706
of a warrior healer.

15:24.749 --> 15:26.142
His wife threatened that

15:26.186 --> 15:28.188
and sent his narcissism
into a frenzy.

15:28.231 --> 15:31.365
I don't think he's gonna do
well without money and status.

15:31.408 --> 15:32.714
I think he's gonna
look for a way

15:32.757 --> 15:34.281
to keep his business
with Rickman going.

15:34.324 --> 15:36.283
- Brock prescribed
over 3 million pills.

15:36.326 --> 15:37.501
You think someone
would've noticed

15:37.545 --> 15:38.720
and picked up the phone:

15:38.763 --> 15:40.026
the drug company
or a pharmacist.

15:40.069 --> 15:41.766
- Cha-ching.

15:41.810 --> 15:44.160
They all had reason
to look the other way.

15:44.204 --> 15:46.380
- And maybe keep looking
the other way.

15:46.423 --> 15:48.251
If Brock is gonna keep
his business going

15:48.295 --> 15:50.427
he'll need pills.
Oxynet.

15:50.471 --> 15:53.169
We need to visit
with the local sales rep.

15:57.086 --> 15:59.175
Hey, Kenny.
You got a moment?

15:59.219 --> 16:00.524
- [sighs]

16:00.568 --> 16:02.396
[dramatic music]

16:02.439 --> 16:04.615
- I know.
My bad.

16:04.659 --> 16:07.444
I laid in to that guy
a little hard.

16:07.488 --> 16:09.403
Won't happen again.

16:09.446 --> 16:11.753
- I thought you had this
under control.

16:11.796 --> 16:13.798
If you need a refresher course
in anger management,

16:13.842 --> 16:15.365
we can make that happen.

16:16.627 --> 16:18.238
You sleepin' okay?

16:18.281 --> 16:20.805
- Yeah.
Mostly.

16:22.111 --> 16:23.417
- I count on you, Kenny.

16:23.460 --> 16:25.506
That goes both ways.

16:25.549 --> 16:28.596
You need anything,
you let me know.

16:28.639 --> 16:32.513
♪

16:34.645 --> 16:36.778
- He was pilfering my desk.

16:36.821 --> 16:39.607
- He was trying to make it
look like a robbery.

16:39.650 --> 16:41.652
- That's what you say, but
he was reaching for his gun,

16:41.696 --> 16:43.132
and he was gonna shoot me.

16:44.133 --> 16:46.527
- Glenn always was twitchy.
- [sighs]

16:46.570 --> 16:48.181
Lilian was still alive
for God's sake,

16:48.224 --> 16:50.270
he couldn't even do that right.

16:50.313 --> 16:51.575
Woman's gonna ruin my empire.

16:51.619 --> 16:55.275
♪

16:55.318 --> 16:58.452
- Your empire.

16:58.495 --> 17:00.584
I don't know why I don't
just throw you in that hole

17:00.628 --> 17:02.108
with your car.

17:02.151 --> 17:05.154
- Because we're still partners.
- Mm.

17:05.198 --> 17:08.156
- I have another plan.
One last score.

17:09.897 --> 17:12.204
Then I can disappear
to some out of the way place

17:12.248 --> 17:15.556
where they appreciate a doctor
with my qualifications.

17:16.557 --> 17:18.733
- Brock.

17:18.776 --> 17:21.474
New phones.

17:21.518 --> 17:23.390
New name.

17:26.784 --> 17:29.613
Time to shed your old skin.

17:35.184 --> 17:38.144
- A strip club?

17:38.187 --> 17:39.493
- This is where the sales rep

17:39.536 --> 17:41.538
takes the doctors
to talk business.

17:41.582 --> 17:43.584
- ♪ You gotta give it to me,
right here ♪

17:43.627 --> 17:45.455
♪ And if you want me, baby

17:45.499 --> 17:46.674
- Right over there.

17:46.717 --> 17:48.284
- Which one of the two
is Sydney Lane?

17:48.328 --> 17:50.156
- The one giving the lap dance.

17:50.199 --> 17:51.853
The two men are doctors.

17:52.941 --> 17:55.552
Sydney used to be a stripper
before she was a sales rep.

17:55.596 --> 17:57.641
- You were keeping that
from me, weren't you?

17:57.685 --> 18:00.166
- Ms. Lane.
FBI.

18:00.209 --> 18:02.951
Sorry to interrupt
your sales presentation.

18:02.994 --> 18:05.258
Can we speak to you outside
for a minute?

18:08.739 --> 18:11.220
- This is about Dr. Brock.
What about him?

18:11.264 --> 18:12.526
He was my top prescriber.

18:12.569 --> 18:14.354
- 3 million pills
over four years?

18:14.397 --> 18:16.443
That's drug pushing,
not prescribing.

18:16.486 --> 18:18.358
- Not my problem.

18:18.401 --> 18:20.882
I'm paid to get doctors to
prescribe my company's product.

18:20.925 --> 18:22.797
- By grinding yourself
in their lap?

18:22.840 --> 18:24.712
- That's why the company
recruited me,

18:24.755 --> 18:26.931
and six other exotic dancers
I know of.

18:26.975 --> 18:28.890
- I'm sure you've heard what
Brock is accused of,

18:28.933 --> 18:30.718
not to mention his pill mill.

18:30.761 --> 18:32.198
He might need some money,
he might reach out to you.

18:32.241 --> 18:33.764
- Pill mill?
[laughs]

18:33.808 --> 18:35.810
Until a nonaddictive
painkiller as good as opioids

18:35.853 --> 18:38.900
hits the market,
every practice is a pill mill.

18:38.943 --> 18:40.467
Even with Brock
out of business

18:40.510 --> 18:42.251
the wholesale pharmacist
from my territory

18:42.295 --> 18:43.774
just doubled his order
of Oxynet.

18:45.254 --> 18:46.342
- Doubled?

18:47.822 --> 18:49.606
Three days after your top
prescriber went on the run?

18:51.260 --> 18:52.957
- There's a whole lot of pain
out there.

18:54.481 --> 18:56.613
You think
maybe this wholesaler

18:56.657 --> 18:58.485
could be in business
with Brock?

18:58.528 --> 19:00.226
Maybe selling him pills out of
the back of his warehouse?

19:00.269 --> 19:01.923
- With the regulatory agencies
breathing down his neck?

19:01.966 --> 19:03.272
I don't think so.

19:04.621 --> 19:08.234
- But a robbery, that would be
easier to explain.

19:08.277 --> 19:10.714
Wouldn't it?
- Easier.

19:11.759 --> 19:14.414
- And when does this shipment
of Oxynet come in?

19:14.457 --> 19:18.374
[eerie music]

19:18.418 --> 19:21.595
- Let's go!
Let's go!

19:21.638 --> 19:23.336
We got ten minutes
before the next shift comes in.

19:23.379 --> 19:24.641
Let's go, prospect, move it.

19:24.685 --> 19:25.903
Move it.

19:25.947 --> 19:28.950
[tires squealing]

19:31.648 --> 19:33.259
- Freeze!
- FBI!

19:33.302 --> 19:35.391
Hands up!
- Get down, get down!

19:35.435 --> 19:37.045
- Get down on your knees!
- Get down!

19:37.088 --> 19:38.786
- Get down on the ground now!
[indistinct shouting]

19:38.829 --> 19:40.353
- Where I can see 'em!

19:40.396 --> 19:41.745
- Put the box down!
[engine revving]

19:42.006 --> 19:42.964
- Put it down!

19:43.007 --> 19:45.445
[gunshot, man grunts]

19:47.664 --> 19:50.406
- Don't move.
Find Brock!

19:50.450 --> 19:53.801
- Let's get out of here.
- I'm not leaving my brothers.

19:53.844 --> 19:55.803
- Screw you.
- Hey!

19:55.846 --> 19:57.370
I said we're stayin'.

19:58.632 --> 20:00.634
- I'm not going to jail
for this.

20:00.677 --> 20:03.289
[police radio chatter]

20:03.332 --> 20:05.900
- No sign of Brock.
- Just these knuckleheads.

20:05.943 --> 20:07.641
I barely put a finger on them,
boss.

20:07.684 --> 20:09.382
- This is Victor-7.

20:09.425 --> 20:11.297
I have a DB in a vehicle
at Sweeney and Glover.

20:11.340 --> 20:13.734
Looks like multiple GSWs.

20:13.777 --> 20:20.784
♪

20:23.526 --> 20:25.006
- The door was like this:
open?

20:25.049 --> 20:26.050
- Yes, sir.

20:33.449 --> 20:36.670
- Nine mil.
Same caliber Brock uses.

20:43.764 --> 20:45.113
- [inhales]

20:45.156 --> 20:47.681
Brock's wife wanted a divorce.

20:47.724 --> 20:50.510
She threatened to snitch
on his side business

20:50.553 --> 20:52.816
unless he gave her a good deal,

20:52.860 --> 20:58.126
but he said he would never
split his empire with her, so--

20:58.169 --> 20:59.606
[clicks tongue]

20:59.649 --> 21:01.608
- His side business,
the pill mill?

21:01.651 --> 21:03.523
Is that why
she wanted a divorce?

21:03.566 --> 21:05.002
- I don't think
that bothered her.

21:05.046 --> 21:07.135
I mean, she introduced me
to Brock,

21:07.178 --> 21:09.877
and she knew that
I was no angel,

21:09.920 --> 21:12.619
but you know, so long as
I supported the vets

21:12.662 --> 21:14.621
and Brock was raking it in.

21:14.664 --> 21:16.057
- So why leave him?

21:16.100 --> 21:17.885
We heard Brock spoiled her.

21:17.928 --> 21:19.365
- I don't know.

21:19.408 --> 21:23.107
I never got the chance
to ask her.

21:23.151 --> 21:25.414
- Okay, Rickman, new question:

21:25.458 --> 21:27.895
What's Brock's next move?
Where does he go?

21:27.938 --> 21:31.377
- You are the FBI.
If you don't know--

21:31.420 --> 21:34.118
- You're a fountain
of no knowledge, aren't you?

21:34.162 --> 21:36.077
For this you gave him a break
on his sentencing?

21:36.120 --> 21:38.645
- Agent LaCroix--
- This charade

21:38.688 --> 21:40.908
that he didn't know
Brock hired one of his men

21:40.951 --> 21:42.866
to kill his wife?
It's bull!

21:42.910 --> 21:46.000
♪

21:46.043 --> 21:48.394
You conspired
to kill a witness

21:48.437 --> 21:50.831
to an interstate
drug operation.

21:50.874 --> 21:54.443
You should be up
for the death penalty.

21:57.011 --> 21:58.708
[hisses]
- Mm.

22:00.623 --> 22:03.409
- Okay, take a deep breath.

22:03.452 --> 22:05.454
- They expect us to dance a
minuet with that piece of dirt?

22:05.498 --> 22:06.673
He doesn't
want Brock found!

22:06.716 --> 22:08.152
Brock could be a witness
against him.

22:08.196 --> 22:09.545
- Agent LaCroix!

22:09.589 --> 22:11.417
- Don't you
cut a deal with him!

22:11.460 --> 22:13.680
We'll find Brock
without him.

22:13.723 --> 22:16.639
- Now we know why you didn't
take a desk job at 26 Fed.

22:23.864 --> 22:26.736
- [breathing heavily]

22:26.780 --> 22:28.825
- Leslie.

22:28.869 --> 22:30.914
Thanks for coming.

22:30.958 --> 22:32.612
You didn't tell your daughter,
did you?

22:32.655 --> 22:34.744
- No, no.
Doctor.

22:34.788 --> 22:37.747
It was so thoughtful of you
to reach out to me.

22:37.791 --> 22:40.097
- I don't forget my patients.

22:40.141 --> 22:43.536
I know you've been sick,
so I brought you your medicine.

22:43.579 --> 22:45.146
- Thank you.

22:45.189 --> 22:47.714
I don't believe what they say
about you.

22:49.193 --> 22:51.152
- Yeah, well,

22:51.195 --> 22:53.676
it's all a misunderstanding.

22:59.987 --> 23:03.512
- Oh, your hands are shaking.
Let me help.

23:09.736 --> 23:13.174
- [breathing heavily]

23:13.217 --> 23:15.959
You got a good heart.

23:16.003 --> 23:17.918
I know it.

23:21.182 --> 23:23.576
[sighs]

23:23.619 --> 23:26.622
N--no, no.
That feels good.

23:28.232 --> 23:30.931
- I won't let anything bad
happen to you.

23:31.714 --> 23:33.803
- [wheezing]

23:33.847 --> 23:36.893
[ominous music]

23:36.937 --> 23:43.944
♪

23:50.341 --> 23:52.735
- He lost his accomplices.
He's on his own.

23:52.779 --> 23:53.954
He'll run out of moves.

23:53.997 --> 23:55.521
- He served in Bosnia.

23:55.564 --> 23:57.261
Probably not the first
tight spot he's been in.

23:57.305 --> 23:58.785
- That was a long time ago.

23:58.828 --> 24:00.221
He's grown used
to his comforts.

24:00.264 --> 24:03.529
Hey, it's Tali
out in the back field.

24:03.572 --> 24:06.140
Your father took it
this afternoon.

24:06.183 --> 24:07.750
Every day after school,

24:07.794 --> 24:09.230
she's out there looking
for this bird we released.

24:09.273 --> 24:12.059
She's a funny one.
- Are we doing photos?

24:12.102 --> 24:14.322
Here's Anais at the park
last Sunday.

24:14.365 --> 24:15.845
She loved the ducks.

24:15.889 --> 24:17.064
She wanted
to go swimming with them.

24:17.107 --> 24:19.675
- I remember when Tali
was this age.

24:19.719 --> 24:21.547
It was--

24:21.590 --> 24:23.070
well, special, right?

24:23.113 --> 24:24.767
- I've got a live feed
of my clownfish.

24:24.811 --> 24:26.726
Wanna see?
- Yeah, I wanna see 'em,

24:26.769 --> 24:28.249
covered in beer batter
and deep fried.

24:28.292 --> 24:30.556
- Shut up.
- [laughs]

24:30.599 --> 24:32.296
- [sighs]

24:32.340 --> 24:33.994
I don't think
it's about the bird, bro.

24:34.037 --> 24:37.911
[dramatic music]

24:37.954 --> 24:39.347
[computer dings]

24:39.390 --> 24:41.044
- There's a purchase
at a jewelry store

24:41.088 --> 24:43.612
that just dropped
on Brock's AmEx corporate card.

24:43.656 --> 24:45.135
25 grand
the day he killed his wife.

24:45.179 --> 24:46.572
Bullock Jewelers,
Richmond, Virginia.

24:46.615 --> 24:48.312
- A gift for a girlfriend

24:48.356 --> 24:50.837
charged to his corporate card
so his wife wouldn't see it.

24:50.880 --> 24:52.360
- Any other hooks to Richmond?

24:52.403 --> 24:54.101
- Yeah, a dozen calls
to a Richmond cell phone

24:54.144 --> 24:55.624
registered
to his New York clinic.

24:55.668 --> 24:57.104
- I'm seeing three flights
to Richmond

24:57.147 --> 24:59.106
in the past year,
all paid in cash.

24:59.149 --> 25:00.716
- Sounds like he was trying
to keep an affair

25:00.760 --> 25:02.283
under his wife's radar.

25:02.326 --> 25:04.285
- Call the jewelry store.
Find out who the lucky girl is.

25:07.810 --> 25:10.117
- [heavy breathing]

25:10.160 --> 25:12.685
- Megan Curtis?

25:12.728 --> 25:15.775
I'm Agent Barnes,
this is Agent LaCroix.

25:15.818 --> 25:17.254
- It's about my father,
isn't it?

25:19.996 --> 25:22.346
Justin Brock?
- Your father?

25:23.434 --> 25:25.698
You mind if we talk
in your apartment?

25:25.741 --> 25:27.351
- Yeah.

25:27.395 --> 25:30.050
Curtis is my mom's maiden name.

25:30.093 --> 25:32.139
Started using it
after my parents got divorced.

25:32.182 --> 25:33.706
- You angry at your dad?

25:33.749 --> 25:35.142
- I was ten.
You know, I was a kid.

25:35.185 --> 25:37.623
I didn't know there were
two sides to every story.

25:37.666 --> 25:39.407
You can take a good look.
He's not here.

25:40.408 --> 25:42.192
- We didn't think he would be.

25:42.236 --> 25:44.368
Have you been in touch
with him?

25:44.412 --> 25:46.414
- No, no, we don't talk
that often.

25:46.457 --> 25:48.155
I've only seen him twice
this year.

25:48.198 --> 25:50.418
He was supposed to come down
for my graduation next week.

25:52.463 --> 25:53.987
Bought me a bracelet.

25:54.030 --> 25:55.728
- We saw that.

25:55.771 --> 25:58.339
The jewelry store
has it on hold for you.

25:58.382 --> 26:00.080
- We also noticed he liked to
cover his tracks

26:00.123 --> 26:01.821
whenever he flew down here.

26:01.864 --> 26:04.127
- That's because of his wife.
She was very possessive.

26:04.171 --> 26:06.260
It was a whole soap opera.

26:06.303 --> 26:08.001
- Can't have been
easy for you.

26:08.044 --> 26:09.350
Can't be easy for you now

26:09.393 --> 26:10.917
with your father accused
of killing his wife.

26:10.960 --> 26:12.875
- I don't believe that
for a second.

26:12.919 --> 26:14.921
- What do you think
happened?

26:17.053 --> 26:19.708
- Lilian introduced him
to some bad people.

26:19.752 --> 26:22.015
They used him,
they killed Lilian,

26:22.058 --> 26:24.452
and they would have killed him
too if he hadn't run away.

26:24.495 --> 26:26.236
- He's lucky to have you
in his corner.

26:27.237 --> 26:29.849
- [laughs]
I'm the lucky one.

26:29.892 --> 26:31.851
My dad's a hero.

26:31.894 --> 26:34.114
He inspired me
to join the ROTC.

26:38.248 --> 26:41.382
I interviewed him
for this essay in high school

26:41.425 --> 26:45.038
about his service in Bosnia.
It was awesome.

26:45.081 --> 26:46.822
It was something
he never talked about

26:46.866 --> 26:49.695
when I was growing up.
He's so humble.

26:49.738 --> 26:51.131
It's--he even told me
not to say anything to Gramps

26:51.174 --> 26:53.742
about my essay.
- You mean his father?

26:54.743 --> 26:56.223
Why not?

26:56.266 --> 26:58.486
- Gramps is a veteran too.

26:58.529 --> 27:01.402
Dad didn't wanna make it
look like he was bragging.

27:02.795 --> 27:04.884
That's the type of person
he is.

27:04.927 --> 27:09.018
♪

27:09.062 --> 27:10.890
- In case he tries to
get in touch with you,

27:10.933 --> 27:14.458
Megan, it really is better
for him if he turns himself in.

27:19.159 --> 27:21.204
- [sighs]

27:22.249 --> 27:24.207
- [sighs]
It's nice to have heroes.

27:24.251 --> 27:25.426
- "Humble."

27:25.469 --> 27:26.949
Not a word
I'd associate with Brock.

27:26.993 --> 27:28.777
- His old man
lives in Norfolk.

27:29.865 --> 27:31.911
- Justin wouldn't reach out
to his dad.

27:31.954 --> 27:33.086
He knows better.

27:33.129 --> 27:34.914
[whispers] Right there.

27:34.957 --> 27:37.133
It's just some people
from church.

27:39.875 --> 27:41.790
[whispers] Let's go in there.

27:44.227 --> 27:48.275
Frank had a stroke a year ago.
He's on assisted breathing.

27:48.318 --> 27:50.930
He can't speak.
He can't walk.

27:50.973 --> 27:53.062
I haven't told him
about Justin.

27:53.106 --> 27:54.585
It'd probably kill him.

27:57.066 --> 27:59.373
- Those photos,
those are all Frank?

27:59.416 --> 28:04.117
- Yes, he was decorated
for his service in Vietnam.

28:04.160 --> 28:05.858
- You said that Dr. Brock
knew better

28:05.901 --> 28:07.424
than to ask
his father for help.

28:07.468 --> 28:10.253
Is that because of the stroke,
or something else?

28:11.385 --> 28:14.431
- Nothing Justin ever did
was good enough for Frank,

28:14.475 --> 28:16.477
no matter the success.

28:16.520 --> 28:19.088
It just broke my heart.

28:23.179 --> 28:24.398
- [sighs]

28:24.441 --> 28:26.139
That's a Bronze Star, isn't it?

28:26.182 --> 28:29.142
- Yes!
Were you in the service?

28:29.185 --> 28:31.535
- No, no, my wife.

28:31.579 --> 28:33.407
Army intel, Afghanistan 2016.

28:33.450 --> 28:35.496
She didn't come back.

28:35.539 --> 28:37.890
- I'm sorry.

28:37.933 --> 28:39.413
- Thank you.

28:39.456 --> 28:42.503
[dramatic music]

28:42.546 --> 28:45.811
- You know, Dr. Brock won
a Bronze Star too,

28:45.854 --> 28:47.160
in Bosnia.

28:47.987 --> 28:50.163
- He did?
- You didn't know?

28:51.033 --> 28:52.339
- No.

28:52.382 --> 28:54.036
I didn't know
he was in the service.

28:54.080 --> 28:56.343
I mean,
Frank never told me,

28:56.386 --> 28:59.041
but then Frank never
had anything positive to say

28:59.085 --> 29:00.477
about Justin.

29:04.264 --> 29:07.223
- Most of my psych classes are
about boys and their mommies,

29:07.267 --> 29:09.008
but boys and their daddies?
[sighs]

29:09.051 --> 29:10.879
That is a higher level
of screwed up.

29:10.923 --> 29:13.055
You'd think Brock's service'd
be the one thing

29:13.099 --> 29:14.840
his old man'd be proud of.

29:14.883 --> 29:16.885
- Brock was more interested
in displaying his medal

29:16.929 --> 29:18.191
than wearing it.

29:18.234 --> 29:19.540
He was puffing himself out.

29:19.583 --> 29:21.455
The photos, the money,
the status,

29:21.498 --> 29:24.240
he was proving to himself he's
worth his father's respect.

29:25.894 --> 29:27.635
I wonder how far he went.

29:30.072 --> 29:32.074
- You would not believe
the hoops I had to jump through

29:32.118 --> 29:33.510
to get his service records.

29:33.554 --> 29:35.338
Brock was enlisted in '95.

29:35.382 --> 29:37.471
After four months
he was medically discharged

29:37.514 --> 29:39.342
with something called
Optic Neuritis.

29:39.386 --> 29:41.431
- Sounds serious.
- It's just an infection.

29:41.475 --> 29:43.564
Couple months on steroids,
and you're back in business.

29:43.607 --> 29:46.045
- It's an off ramp
out of boot camp.

29:46.088 --> 29:47.350
Brock couldn't hack it.

29:47.394 --> 29:48.961
- He never went back?

29:49.004 --> 29:50.310
- No record he did.

29:50.353 --> 29:53.052
- Stolen valor.
That son of a bitch

29:53.095 --> 29:54.880
pretended to be a veteran
to impress his wife.

29:54.923 --> 29:57.056
- I think she was on to him.

29:57.099 --> 29:59.580
I found an FOI request
in this file from her

29:59.623 --> 30:01.190
from a month ago.

30:01.234 --> 30:02.888
She was looking for
his military records.

30:02.931 --> 30:04.237
- The veteran
she fell in love with?

30:04.280 --> 30:05.325
That explains the divorce.

30:05.368 --> 30:07.283
- State cops.

30:07.327 --> 30:08.937
It's about
one of Brock's patients.

30:10.678 --> 30:13.289
- She was found early this
morning dead of an overdose.

30:13.333 --> 30:15.683
Her car is missing.
Syringe was still in her arm,

30:15.726 --> 30:18.077
with a partial thumbprint
belonging to Brock.

30:18.120 --> 30:20.427
- He killed her for her car.
He didn't have to do that.

30:20.470 --> 30:21.950
- His patients are
just things to him.

30:21.994 --> 30:24.126
Obstacles.

30:27.390 --> 30:30.263
[somber music]

30:30.306 --> 30:37.313
♪

30:40.534 --> 30:42.318
- Hey, her car was just found
abandoned

30:42.362 --> 30:44.016
outside of Harrisburg.

30:44.059 --> 30:45.626
He's smart.
He's mixing it up.

30:45.669 --> 30:48.237
- I'll get the video footage
from bus stations in that area.

30:48.281 --> 30:51.284
- Hey boss, just got the
phone dumps off Megan's cell.

30:51.327 --> 30:52.981
So last two days,
she got three calls

30:53.025 --> 30:54.983
from a burner in New York.

30:55.027 --> 30:56.376
- That's gotta be Brock.

30:56.419 --> 30:58.204
- Uh-huh.
And get this.

30:58.247 --> 31:00.075
Same burner,
coming from Maryland.

31:00.119 --> 31:01.468
He's heading south towards her.

31:01.511 --> 31:07.517
♪

31:16.135 --> 31:17.876
- I have finals tomorrow.
I can't talk to you.

31:17.919 --> 31:19.138
I have to study.

31:19.181 --> 31:20.400
- This is your father's
military record.

31:20.443 --> 31:22.097
You should read it.

31:24.839 --> 31:26.232
- I don't understand.

31:26.275 --> 31:28.060
- He never made it
out of basic training.

31:28.103 --> 31:31.019
- No Bosnia,
no medals, no heroics.

31:31.063 --> 31:33.021
It's a fantasy he created
to seduce his new wife;

31:33.065 --> 31:35.067
maybe even rehabilitate himself
in your eyes.

31:36.242 --> 31:38.026
- No.
It's a mistake.

31:38.070 --> 31:40.072
- No, no mistake.
His life was a fabrication.

31:40.115 --> 31:41.725
- The only medicine
he practiced

31:41.769 --> 31:43.466
was prescribing opioids
to addicts.

31:43.510 --> 31:45.816
- This is one of
your father's patients.

31:45.860 --> 31:48.123
[dramatic music]

31:48.167 --> 31:50.821
This is when
she started seeing your father.

31:51.822 --> 31:54.913
This is six months later when
she was arrested for a DWI.

31:54.956 --> 31:57.176
This is yesterday

31:57.219 --> 32:00.048
where your father left her
after he stole her car.

32:00.092 --> 32:02.224
The syringe had
his fingerprints on it.

32:02.268 --> 32:07.186
♪

32:07.229 --> 32:08.927
Look at her, Megan.

32:10.929 --> 32:12.365
Look at her.

32:14.193 --> 32:16.369
She has a 16-year-old daughter,
Cassie.

32:16.412 --> 32:18.762
Cassie has lived through
her mother's addiction,

32:18.806 --> 32:21.026
an addiction your father
monetized to pay for his cars,

32:21.069 --> 32:23.245
his vacation,
your bracelet--

32:33.995 --> 32:36.302
I know what it's like
to be disappointed by a parent;

32:36.345 --> 32:38.565
To find out he's not who you
thought he was, but...

32:42.003 --> 32:43.309
You have to face it, Megan.

32:46.486 --> 32:48.444
- Help us.
Please.

32:48.488 --> 32:50.185
We think your father's
coming here.

32:50.229 --> 32:52.144
We wanna get him into custody
without hurting him.

32:52.187 --> 32:53.972
- I don't wanna hear it.

32:54.581 --> 32:57.453
I have exams.
I work a part-time job.

32:57.497 --> 33:01.153
I--I have to find a real job.
Just please...

33:02.154 --> 33:05.157
Please, just leave me alone.

33:09.596 --> 33:11.554
- So much for tough love.

33:11.598 --> 33:14.122
Maybe you rubbed it in her face
a little bit too hard.

33:14.166 --> 33:15.341
- I wouldn't have done it

33:15.384 --> 33:18.039
if I didn't think
she could handle it.

33:18.083 --> 33:20.128
She can't avoid the truth.
She has to live through it.

33:20.172 --> 33:21.912
It's the only way.

33:21.956 --> 33:23.827
Brock's not coming here
for her graduation.

33:23.871 --> 33:27.309
There's something he needs.
Something from her.

33:27.353 --> 33:30.008
- We found three 529
investment accounts

33:30.051 --> 33:31.226
in the name Megan Curtis.

33:31.270 --> 33:33.141
- Yes, those are
federal tax-deferred

33:33.185 --> 33:34.882
college savings plans.

33:34.925 --> 33:37.406
- Who set up the accounts?
Can you look that up?

33:37.450 --> 33:39.017
Now?

33:41.976 --> 33:44.631
[keys clacking]

33:45.284 --> 33:48.113
- Here, the accounts
were opened by Justin Brock

33:48.156 --> 33:49.897
three years ago.

33:51.203 --> 33:52.900
- There's almost two million
dollars in here.

33:52.943 --> 33:55.859
- Has Ms. Curtis
accessed this money?

33:55.903 --> 33:58.036
- No, Ms. Curtis
has never contacted us.

33:58.079 --> 34:00.255
- The way she was sweating
finding a job,

34:00.299 --> 34:01.865
maybe she doesn't know
about the money.

34:01.909 --> 34:03.389
- And Brock is blocked
from accessing it.

34:03.432 --> 34:05.173
- Yes, we got an alert on him

34:05.217 --> 34:07.523
from FIN-cen two days ago
barring him.

34:07.567 --> 34:09.917
- But not his daughter.

34:09.960 --> 34:11.310
He needs her
to get to this money.

34:11.353 --> 34:12.398
That's why he's coming here.

34:17.098 --> 34:19.969
- [sighs]
I told you to leave me alone.

34:22.364 --> 34:23.539
- Does your father know
how hard you work

34:23.583 --> 34:24.931
to put yourself
through school;

34:24.975 --> 34:26.281
to earn
your officer's commission?

34:28.196 --> 34:30.545
You think he gave you that
bracelet because he cares?

34:33.158 --> 34:35.333
Your father hid $2 million
under your name

34:35.377 --> 34:37.161
in an investment bank
here in Richmond.

34:42.254 --> 34:44.081
- It's money
from his drug operation.

34:48.476 --> 34:50.130
- He didn't tell you, did he?

34:50.175 --> 34:51.610
While you scraped by.

34:53.178 --> 34:55.571
He needs that money to escape.

34:55.614 --> 34:57.660
He can't get to it now,
but you can.

34:59.532 --> 35:01.316
That's why he's coming here.

35:01.360 --> 35:05.233
♪

35:05.277 --> 35:08.018
It's not about you.

35:08.062 --> 35:09.368
It's about the money.

35:14.286 --> 35:16.157
I'm sorry, Megan.

35:18.159 --> 35:19.726
Can you help us?

35:24.078 --> 35:25.253
- Can't imagine
what she's feeling.

35:25.297 --> 35:27.037
- I got a good idea.

35:27.081 --> 35:29.127
Probably what my mother felt
after my old man gambled away

35:29.170 --> 35:31.607
the college money she'd saved
for my sister and me.

35:33.174 --> 35:36.090
It's time to give Brock a taste
of what that feels like.

35:45.012 --> 35:47.188
[foreboding music]

35:47.232 --> 35:49.190
[keys clacking]

35:49.234 --> 35:53.107
♪

35:53.151 --> 35:55.283
- Clinton's in position
outside Megan's.

35:55.327 --> 35:57.633
- Somebody accessed
the accounts.

36:14.650 --> 36:16.478
[keys clack]

36:21.440 --> 36:28.316
[phone ringing]

36:28.360 --> 36:30.057
- Tax-deferred.

36:30.100 --> 36:31.711
- Chuck Reid.

36:31.754 --> 36:35.193
- Mr. Reid is in a meeting
off-site, but I can help you.

36:35.236 --> 36:36.585
- There's a problem
with my 529 accounts.

36:36.629 --> 36:38.196
- I'll need
one of the account numbers.

36:40.241 --> 36:43.679
- GR1431120.

36:43.723 --> 36:45.681
Name on the account
is Megan Curtis.

36:45.725 --> 36:48.771
- Mother's maiden name?
- Curtis.

36:48.815 --> 36:50.686
My name is Justin Brock.

36:50.730 --> 36:52.688
I'm authorized on the account.

36:52.732 --> 36:55.213
- I see that.
How can I help?

36:55.256 --> 36:57.519
- These accounts are showing
a zero balance.

36:57.563 --> 36:59.347
Why is that?

36:59.391 --> 37:01.219
I had a significant amount
of money in these accounts.

37:01.262 --> 37:02.350
What happened?

37:02.394 --> 37:05.092
- I'm sorry.
Let me check.

37:11.272 --> 37:13.274
- The beneficiary, Ms. Curtis,
came in yesterday

37:13.318 --> 37:15.102
and wired the funds out.

37:15.145 --> 37:17.539
- She wired the funds where?

37:17.583 --> 37:20.150
- I can't release
that information.

37:20.194 --> 37:21.543
- That little bitch.

37:21.587 --> 37:23.110
- What was that, sir?

37:23.153 --> 37:24.720
- His arrogance worked
in our favor.

37:24.764 --> 37:26.244
He never saw us coming.

37:30.422 --> 37:32.293
[line trills]

37:32.337 --> 37:34.077
- This is Megan.
I can't answer the phone

37:34.121 --> 37:36.123
right now, but
if you leave your name and n--

37:48.657 --> 37:50.616
- On the pick-up.
- Copy.

37:52.139 --> 37:53.445
[tires squealing]

38:06.327 --> 38:07.589
[tires squealing]

38:07.633 --> 38:09.461
- Megan!
Here!

38:14.770 --> 38:17.338
- Get back!
What did you do with it?

38:17.382 --> 38:19.427
- Drop the gun now.
- Hey.

38:19.471 --> 38:21.647
- Drop it.
- No.

38:21.690 --> 38:23.518
You get out of my way.
She's coming with me.

38:23.562 --> 38:25.128
- Let her go, Doctor.

38:25.172 --> 38:27.348
- Setting me up?
Your own father?

38:27.392 --> 38:29.263
- Talk to me, Doc.

38:29.307 --> 38:30.656
- I'm not going to jail
for this.

38:30.699 --> 38:32.310
- Let her go, and we can talk.

38:32.353 --> 38:34.616
- No.
No, no.

38:34.660 --> 38:35.791
She's coming with me.

38:35.835 --> 38:37.315
Hey!
- Aah!

38:38.359 --> 38:41.362
[both breathing heavily]

38:41.406 --> 38:44.322
- Give me one good reason
why I shouldn't kill you.

38:44.365 --> 38:46.236
- Megan, don't.

38:46.280 --> 38:47.934
- I looked up to you.

38:48.804 --> 38:50.415
[crying]
You were my hero.

38:51.894 --> 38:53.461
It was all fake--

38:53.505 --> 38:55.202
- Listen to me--

38:55.245 --> 38:58.901
- Everything that I am, you
took from me with your lies.

38:58.945 --> 39:00.729
[crying]

39:00.773 --> 39:02.862
I have nothing!

39:02.905 --> 39:05.343
- Megan, don't do it!
Listen to me, Megan.

39:05.386 --> 39:07.170
- [sobs]

39:07.214 --> 39:08.302
- You can get it back...

39:10.435 --> 39:12.175
But not if you kill him.

39:12.219 --> 39:14.395
You do that,
you lose it all forever.

39:14.439 --> 39:15.744
- Megan, please, don't.
I'm sorry!

39:15.788 --> 39:17.616
- Shut up!
Shut up!

39:19.444 --> 39:21.359
- Look at me, Megan.

39:23.404 --> 39:25.624
- [breathing heavily]

39:25.667 --> 39:27.190
- Megan...

39:27.234 --> 39:30.368
[dramatic music]

39:30.411 --> 39:32.674
You're graduating next week.

39:32.718 --> 39:35.416
You did that.
You did the work, not him.

39:35.460 --> 39:38.463
♪

39:38.506 --> 39:41.901
You're starting a new life--
your life, a good life.

39:42.815 --> 39:45.252
Don't let your anger at him
take that away from you.

39:45.992 --> 39:48.516
- [heavy breathing]

39:48.560 --> 39:49.909
- You're gonna be okay.

39:52.738 --> 39:55.610
Now, just give me the gun.

39:55.654 --> 39:58.657
- [heavy breathing]

40:05.446 --> 40:08.275
[crying]

40:11.757 --> 40:12.932
- [grunting]

40:12.975 --> 40:15.325
- Get up.

40:28.774 --> 40:30.558
- Justin Brock,
you're under arrest

40:30.602 --> 40:32.386
pursuant to
a federal fugitive warrant.

40:32.430 --> 40:33.866
- You like uniforms so much?

40:33.909 --> 40:36.564
We got a nice pretty orange one
you actually deserve.

40:36.608 --> 40:38.000
Come on.

40:48.533 --> 40:50.273
- What's on the menu
for the flight home?

40:50.317 --> 40:53.363
- Local specialties: Sweet
potato soup and spoon bread.

40:53.407 --> 40:55.278
We'll pick it up
on the way to the plane.

40:55.322 --> 40:56.584
- We'll try and
save you some.

40:56.628 --> 40:57.977
- Hey, Kenny.

40:58.020 --> 41:00.936
I meant what I said.
You stay on top of it, okay?

41:00.980 --> 41:02.982
- Yeah.
I got it.

41:07.726 --> 41:09.336
- I hope you're right;

41:09.379 --> 41:10.598
that she'll get through it.

41:10.642 --> 41:11.947
- She will.

41:11.991 --> 41:14.428
She's a lot stronger
than I was at her age.

41:14.472 --> 41:16.474
If her dad had been my dad--
[chuckles]

41:23.350 --> 41:24.656
- There she is.

41:26.396 --> 41:29.356
- Hey, wáten,
how you doing?

41:30.531 --> 41:32.707
- I'm okay, Uncle Clint.

41:32.751 --> 41:35.057
Are you staying for dinner?

41:35.797 --> 41:37.582
- If you're asking, sure.

41:39.671 --> 41:41.411
I'm gonna go talk to the folks.

41:49.028 --> 41:52.510
- So have you seen Wally?

41:52.553 --> 41:54.337
- Nope.

41:54.381 --> 41:57.863
I don't think
he's ever coming back.

42:04.130 --> 42:06.088
[crying]
I miss Mom.

42:06.132 --> 42:10.832
[somber music]

42:10.876 --> 42:12.573
- Yeah.

42:12.617 --> 42:17.491
♪

42:17.535 --> 42:19.711
I miss her too, sweetheart.
